00:00:00.979 --> 00:00:05.020
The Fees and Availability of Elder Care Services
in Marlton, NJ

00:00:05.020 --> 00:00:10.690
The most important aim of several families
is to aid their loved ones reside in their

00:00:10.690 --> 00:00:15.529
own home in a safe and sound and comfortable
environment for as long as possible.

00:00:15.529 --> 00:00:20.990
No one’s favorite option is to go to a facility
or an institution no matter how appealing

00:00:20.990 --> 00:00:23.390
the building or the decorations.

00:00:23.390 --> 00:00:27.710
For a senior to remain in their own property
securely they many need just a number of hours

00:00:27.710 --> 00:00:31.029
of support or they may need around the clock
care.

00:00:31.029 --> 00:00:35.489
An assessment by a home care professional
is needed to identify what is best.

00:00:35.489 --> 00:00:41.260
UNDERSTANDING THE COST OF ELDER CARE SERVICES:
According to the MetLife Mature Market Annual

00:00:41.260 --> 00:00:46.269
Survey on the Cost of Care in the United States,
the findings look like this:

00:00:46.269 --> 00:00:51.609
• The national average daily rate for a
private room in a nursing home rose 4.4% from

00:00:51.609 --> 00:00:57.629
$229 in 2010 to $239 in 2011.

00:00:57.629 --> 00:01:02.730
• The national average monthly base rate
in an assisted living community rose 5.6%

00:01:02.730 --> 00:01:09.970
from $3,293 in 2010 to $3,477 in 2011.

00:01:09.970 --> 00:01:17.020
• The national average daily rate for adult
day services rose 4.5% from $67 in 2010 to

00:01:17.020 --> 00:01:19.830
$70 in 2011.

00:01:19.830 --> 00:01:25.160
• The national average hourly rates for
home health aides ($21) and homemakers ($19)

00:01:25.160 --> 00:01:27.900
were unchanged from 2010.

